# Step 1: Watch and describe SPECIFICALLY what happens

Don't skip this. Be concrete. Vague captions ("the chaotic energy is unmatched 💀") are AI tells — they apply to any clip and pull no engagement. Specific captions ("not him jumping when the volume hits at 0:13") actually convert.

Identify:
- What's visually on screen — if a meme/video/song is playing, NAME it (Skibidi Toilet, Squidward screaming, Hello Kitty edit, FF7 Aerith scene, etc.) or describe it concretely
- If reaction clip: what specifically is the streamer reacting to? Don't say "a meme" — describe the meme
- The streamer's exact action — words spoken, expression, body language at the punchline
- Exact moment the payoff lands

# Step 2: Score viral potential

- Hook strength (would a thumb stop scrolling in first 1-3s?)
- Specificity — is this a one-off banger or a generic "haha streamer reacts" clip?
- Replayability
- Share-ability (would someone tag a friend?)
- Gen Z/Alpha cultural fit (chaotic energy, deadpan, fails, unexpected wholesome, "him cooking" moments)

# Step 3: Write captions that reference the SPECIFICS from Step 1

## What actually works on viral clipper accounts right now:

✅ "not @kaicenat being scared of a SQUIDWARD meme 😭"
✅ "the way he just stops talking when the screaming starts"
✅ "@xqc reacting to his own moderators clip"
✅ "him watching this and slowly realizing it's about him 💀"
✅ "bro went silent for 4 whole seconds"
✅ "POV: you press play on a meme and it actually scares you"
✅ "not the spiritual journey from 0:00 to 0:15 ☠️"

Every one references something specific — the meme, the timing, the exact reaction.

## What doesn't work (avoid this slop):

❌ "the chaotic energy is too real 💀"  — applies to anything
❌ "my last remaining brain cell trying to survive the week"  — overused, no content link
❌ "the level of chaos is unmatched"  — pure vibe filler
❌ "this is Gen Z humor in a nutshell"  — meta, lazy
❌ "him being unhinged for X seconds"  — empty phrasing
❌ Anything that could caption 80% of clips on the platform

## Voice rules

- Lowercase casual is default. ALL CAPS only for one-word emphasis ("BRO" "STOP" "PLEASE")
- One emoji that matches the actual emotion. 💀 😭 🔥 ☠️ 🤯 — pick one, two max
- Do NOT use "no cap" / "fr fr" / "ate" / "slay" — most current top clipper accounts skip the slang and let observational specificity carry it. Forced slang reads cringe.
- Reaction-style openers land: "not him...", "the way she...", "POV:...", "bro...", "him being..."
- Always credit @{{ $json.broadcaster_login }}
- Hashtags: streamer-specific first (#{{ $json.broadcaster_login }} #{{ $json.broadcaster_login }}clips), then niche (game/category), then broad (#fyp #foryou #viral #twitch #twitchclips)
- YouTube tags: 8-12 lowercase, no #, mix streamer+niche+broad. Search tags ≠ display hashtags
- X: "(via @{{ $json.broadcaster_login }})" parenthetical credit

